00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:53,397
[SPEAKER_01]: In general, a community land trust is a nonprofit organization that acquires and holds land for long-term community benefit.

143
00:11:53,757 --> 00:11:58,461
[SPEAKER_01]: So it can be done in a number of different forms or one of a number of different goals.

144
00:11:59,261 --> 00:12:07,287
[SPEAKER_01]: There are some community land trusts that purchase and steward land for the purpose of providing farmland, affordable farmland for people.

145
00:12:07,807 --> 00:12:09,907
[SPEAKER_01]: There are some that just focus on housing.

146
00:12:10,468 --> 00:12:16,129
[SPEAKER_01]: And there are some that kind of spread their goals out over a few different kinds of land stewardship.

147
00:12:16,209 --> 00:12:24,030
[SPEAKER_01]: There are some CLTs that own parks and gardens and farms and housing and have small business space as well.

148
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:32,412
[SPEAKER_01]: So it's a kind of general concept of a nonprofit that holds land for community-driven purposes.

149
00:12:34,452 --> 00:12:42,619
[SPEAKER_01]: So, the CLTs are generally as a nonprofit, they have a board and the board structure is usually 3 parts.

150
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:51,605
[SPEAKER_01]: There's a 3rd or thereabouts that are members of the general community that the community land trust is aiming to be responsible to.

151
00:12:51,806 --> 00:12:53,047
[SPEAKER_01]: That's a geographic area.

152
00:12:53,971 --> 00:13:00,537
[SPEAKER_01]: A third of them are usually people that live in the community land trust housing if it's a housing community land trust.

153
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:05,981
[SPEAKER_01]: And the 3rd are generally community leaders from around the area.

154
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:07,643
[SPEAKER_01]: These can be elected officials.

155
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:12,347
[SPEAKER_01]: They can be leaders of local nonprofits, local advocates and people like that.

156
00:13:12,627 --> 00:13:13,928
[SPEAKER_01]: So it aims to be kind of a.

